        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 4 at 5:46PM PDT by NWS Medford OR</headline>
        <description>At 546 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Seiad Valley, or 11 miles northeast of Happy Camp, moving north at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Seiad Valley and Applegate Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
